  abstract     = {Luxembourg project of law 8307 transposing Directive (EU) 2022/2557 on the resilience of critical entities (CER directive), the operational counterpart of NIS2 covering physical resilience (premises, energy, supply continuity). Deposited at the Chambre des D{\'e}put{\'e}s on 1 September 2023, with rapporteur Laurent Zeimet. Title amended on 29 January 2025. First constitutional vote passed on 28 April 2026 (60 in favour, 0 against, 0 abstentions). Under Luxembourg's combined transposition, every entity classified as critical under PL 8307 is automatically essential under PL 8364 (NIS2). The University of Luxembourg is not, to current knowledge, designated as a CER critical entity, but the framework is part of the regulatory neighbourhood relevant to the present report.},
